<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHammes.2C_Gordon.2C_G.2000">Hammes, Gordon, G. (2000). <i>Thermodynamics and Kinetics for the Biological Sciences</i>. New York: John Wiley &amp; Sons. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0471374911" class="internal">ISBN 0-471-37491-1</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Thermodynamics+and+Kinetics+for+the+Biological+Sciences&amp;rft.aulast=Hammes%2C+Gordon%2C+G.&amp;rft.au=Hammes%2C+Gordon%2C+G.&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=John+Wiley+%26+Sons&amp;rft.isbn=0-471-37491-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_law_of_thermodynamics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHaynie.2C_Donald.2C_T.2001">Haynie, Donald, T. (2001). <i>Biological Thermodynamics</i>. Cambridge: Cambridge University Press. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521795494" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-79549-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Biological+Thermodynamics&amp;rft.aulast=Haynie%2C+Donald%2C+T.&amp;rft.au=Haynie%2C+Donald%2C+T.&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.place=Cambridge&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-79549-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_law_of_thermodynamics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.talkorigins.org/faqs/faq-misconceptions.html#thermo" class="external text" title="http://www.talkorigins.org/faqs/faq-misconceptions.html#thermo" rel="nofollow">Five Major Misconceptions about Evolution</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> doi:10.1098/rspa.2008.0178 "Natural selection for least action", Ville R. I. Kaila and Arto Annila; Proceedings of the Royal Society A.</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite id="CITEREFRennie2002">Rennie, John (2002), "<a href="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000D4FEC-7D5B-1D07-8E49809EC588EEDF" class="external text" title="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000D4FEC-7D5B-1D07-8E49809EC588EEDF" rel="nofollow">15 Answers to Creationist Nonsense</a>", <i>Scientific American</i> <b>287 (1)</b>: 78–85<span class="printonly">, &lt;<a href="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000D4FEC-7D5B-1D07-8E49809EC588EEDF" class="external free" title="http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000D4FEC-7D5B-1D07-8E49809EC588EEDF" rel="nofollow">http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000D4FEC-7D5B-1D07-8E49809EC588EEDF</a>&gt;</span></cite> page 82, accessed <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2007-09-10"><a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a>-<a href="/wiki/September_10" title="September 10">09-10</a></span></li>
</ol>
<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Second_law_of_thermodynamics&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Goldstein, Martin, and Inge F., 1993. <i>The Refrigerator and the Universe</i>. Harvard Univ. Press. Chpts. 4-9 contain an introduction to the Second Law, one a bit less technical than this entry. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780674753242" class="internal">ISBN 978-0674753242</a></li>
<li>Leff, Harvey S., and Rex, Andrew F. (eds.) 2003. <i>Maxwell's Demon 2&#160;: Entropy, classical and quantum information, computing</i>. Bristol UK; Philadelphia PA: Institute of Physics. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780585492377" class="internal">ISBN 978-0585492377</a></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHalliwell1994">Halliwell, J.J. et.al. (1994). <i>Physical Origins of Time Asymmetry</i>. Cambridge. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521568374" class="internal">ISBN 0-521-56837-4</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Physical+Origins+of+Time+Asymmetry&amp;rft.aulast=Halliwell&amp;rft.aufirst=J.J.+et.al.&amp;rft.au=Halliwell%2C+J.J.+et.al.&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge&amp;rft.isbn=0-521-56837-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Second_law_of_thermodynamics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (technical).</li>
</ul>
